editorial:
**Three steps**: (1) Find every match interval `[i, i+w.length-1]` of every word. (2) Merge intervals — *touching counts as overlap* (so adjacent tags fuse). (3) Walk `s`, wrapping each merged span in `<b>...</b>`.

```javascript
function addBoldTag(s, words) {
  const ranges = [];
  for (const w of words) {
    if (!w) continue;
    let i = s.indexOf(w);
    while (i !== -1) {
      ranges.push([i, i + w.length - 1]);
      i = s.indexOf(w, i + 1);
    }
  }
  if (ranges.length === 0) return s;
  ranges.sort((a, b) => a[0] - b[0]);
  const merged = [ranges[0].slice()];
  for (let k = 1; k < ranges.length; k++) {
    const last = merged[merged.length - 1];
    if (ranges[k][0] <= last[1] + 1) {
      last[1] = Math.max(last[1], ranges[k][1]);
    } else {
      merged.push(ranges[k].slice());
    }
  }
  let out = '', p = 0;
  for (const [l, r] of merged) {
    out += s.slice(p, l) + '<b>' + s.slice(l, r + 1) + '</b>';
    p = r + 1;
  }
  out += s.slice(p);
  return out;
}
```

**Time**: O(n*m + k log k) where n = |s|, m = total chars in words, k = match count.
**Space**: O(k + n).

Key twist: merge condition is `start <= lastEnd + 1` (not just `<= lastEnd`) so adjacent ranges fuse — `</b><b>` would otherwise leak through.

